@namespace SpotifyAnalysis.Components

@inject SpotifyMudTheme SpotifyTheme

<MudText>This chart <b>counts words</b> that appear inside artist genres (e.g., "classic rock" → "classic", "rock") for every track on the selected playlists.</MudText>
<MudText>Common words like <i>of</i>, <i>music</i>, etc. are ignored.</MudText>

<MudText Class="mt-4">This means the total can be <b>higher than the number of songs</b> because:</MudText>
<MudList T="string">
	<MudListItem>
		<MudText>One song can have <b>multiple artists</b>.</MudText>
	</MudListItem>
	<MudListItem>
		<MudText>One artist can have <b>several genre labels</b>.</MudText>
	</MudListItem>
	<MudListItem>
		<MudText>Some labels have <b>more than one word</b> (each word is counted).</MudText>
	</MudListItem>
	<MudListItem>
		<MudText>The same word appearing for different artists is <b>counted each time</b>.</MudText>
	</MudListItem>
</MudList>

<MudDivider Class="mt-4 mb-4" />

<MudText >In short, this is a <b>term frequency</b> view over artist genres, not a per‑track tally.</MudText>

<MudText Class="mb-4">Clicking a genre word shows all the tracks contributing to its count.</MudText>


<style>
	b {
		color: @(SpotifyTheme.PaletteDark.Primary.Value);
	}
</style>


